## Authentication — Google OAuth 2.0

### Domain Restriction (critical security rule)
- Only allow Google accounts matching `@[COMPANY_DOMAIN]` (from `process.env.ALLOWED_EMAIL_DOMAIN`)
- Reject all other Google accounts at the OAuth callback — return 403, do not create a session

```typescript
// src/services/auth.service.ts
async function handleOAuthCallback(googleProfile: GoogleProfile): Promise<SessionToken> {
  const domain = googleProfile.email.split('@')[1];
  if (domain !== process.env.ALLOWED_EMAIL_DOMAIN) {
    throw new AppError('Access restricted to company accounts only', 403, 'DOMAIN_RESTRICTED');
  }

  // Check if account is deactivated
  const user = await userRepository.findByEmail(googleProfile.email);
  if (user && !user.isActive) {
    throw new AppError('Your account has been deactivated', 403, 'ACCOUNT_DEACTIVATED');
  }

  // Upsert user (create on first login)
  const upsertedUser = await userRepository.upsertByEmail({
    email: googleProfile.email,
    name: googleProfile.displayName,
    avatarUrl: googleProfile.photos?.[0]?.value,
    clerkId: googleProfile.id,
  });

  return jwtService.sign({ userId: upsertedUser.id, role: upsertedUser.role });
}
```

### JWT / Session Rules
- JWT signed with `process.env.JWT_SECRET` (min 32 chars)
- Access token expiry: `process.env.JWT_EXPIRY` (default: `'7d'`)
- Never store JWT secret in code — environment variable only
- On signout: add token to a denylist (Redis or DB table) until expiry

### Auth Middleware (shared — others import this, never modify)
```typescript
// src/middleware/auth.middleware.ts
export const authenticate = async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  if (!token) return res.status(401).json(errorResponse('Authentication required'));

  try {
    const payload = jwtService.verify(token);
    req.user = payload; // { userId, role }
    next();
  } catch {
    return res.status(401).json(errorResponse('Invalid or expired token'));
  }
};
```

### RBAC Middleware (shared — others import this, never modify)
```typescript
// src/middleware/rbac.middleware.ts
export const requireRole = (...roles: UserRole[]) =>
  (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    if (!roles.includes(req.user?.role)) {
      return res.status(403).json(errorResponse('Insufficient permissions'));
    }
    next();
  };

// Usage in routes
router.get('/admin/users', authenticate, requireRole('Admin'), adminController.listUsers);
router.get('/reviewer/articles/pending', authenticate, requireRole('Reviewer', 'Admin'), reviewerController.listPending);
```

