## Likes

### Business Rules
- Likes are **idempotent** — liking an already-liked article does nothing (no error)
- One like per user per article (enforced by DB primary key)
- Like count is aggregated in article queries (not a separate endpoint)

```typescript
// src/services/like.service.ts
async likeArticle(articleId: string, userId: string): Promise<void> {
  // Idempotent — use INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
  await likeRepository.upsert({ articleId, userId });
}

async unlikeArticle(articleId: string, userId: string): Promise<void> {
  await likeRepository.remove({ articleId, userId });
}
```

