## AI Quiz Generator

### Claude API Integration
- Model: `claude-sonnet-4-6` only — no other models
- API key from `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
- Call via Anthropic SDK: `import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'`
- Quiz generation only allowed on **Published** articles

```typescript
// src/services/quiz.service.ts
import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk';

const anthropic = new Anthropic(); // uses ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env automatically

async generateQuiz(articleId: string): Promise<QuizQuestion[]> {
  const article = await articleRepository.findById(articleId);
  if (!article) throw new AppError('Article not found', 404);
  if (article.status !== 'Published') {
    throw new AppError('Quiz can only be generated for Published articles', 400);
  }

  const prompt = `
    Generate 5 multiple-choice quiz questions based on this article.
    Article Title: ${article.title}
    Article Content: ${extractTextFromTipTap(article.body)}

    Return ONLY a JSON array with this exact structure (no markdown, no explanation):
    [
      {
        "question": "Question text",
        "options": ["A) ...", "B) ...", "C) ...", "D) ..."],
        "correctIndex": 0,
        "explanation": "Brief explanation of correct answer"
      }
    ]
  `;

  const response = await anthropic.messages.create({
    model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6',
    max_tokens: 2000,
    messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }],
  });

  const text = response.content[0].type === 'text' ? response.content[0].text : '';
  return JSON.parse(text) as QuizQuestion[];
}
```

### Quiz Submission Rules
- All questions must be answered before submission — block empty submission
- Score calculated server-side (never trust client-side score)
- After submission, answers cannot be modified
- No re-submission of the same quiz attempt

```typescript
async submitQuiz(attemptData: QuizAttemptInput, userId: string): Promise<QuizResult> {
  const { articleId, questions, answers } = attemptData;

  // Validate all questions answered
  if (answers.length !== questions.length) {
    throw new AppError('All questions must be answered before submission', 400);
  }

  // Server-side scoring
  let correct = 0;
  questions.forEach((q, i) => {
    if (answers[i] === q.correctIndex) correct++;
  });

  const scorePercent = (correct / questions.length) * 100;

  return quizRepository.saveAttempt({
    userId, articleId, questions, answers,
    score: correct, total: questions.length, scorePercent,
  });
}
```

### Quiz UI States (Frontend — Lahiru owns these components)
1. **Initial**: "Generate Quiz" button (visible on Published articles)
2. **Loading**: spinner while Claude API generates
3. **Active**: MCQ questions, one at a time or paginated, answer selection
4. **Confirming**: confirmation modal before submit
5. **Submitted**: result screen (total / correct / incorrect / score % / correct answers revealed)
- "Regenerate Quiz" button available before submission
- After submission: all inputs disabled, result shown
